<TITLE> Exit poll shows India's ruling coalition ahead </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 NEW DELHI, Wed May 13, (bdnews24.com/Reuters) - India's ruling Congress party-led coalition is ahead with 189 to 201 seats in a general election, an exit poll by C-Voter polling agency said after the final day of voting on Wednesday. The poll, covering the month-long election till 0630 GMT (2:30 a.m. EDT) on Wednesday for India TV and UTV Business, forecast 183 to 195 seats for the main opposition Bharatiya Janata Party-led alliance in a 543-member parliament. Either party will need the support of smaller groups to cross the majority mark of 272 seats to form a government, possibly prompting weeks of backroom dealing. India's elections are notoriously hard to predict and most exit polls in the last general election in 2004 were way off the 
